{
 "name": "RPlog_SW1_Log_2000-08-14",
 "title": "Bazil Loses His Mind",
 "summary": "In the auxiliary bay of the NRSC Deliverance, the pilot Vek Eldar reunites with Lelila Jayespyer just as Bazil McKenzie staggers in wrapped in a sheet and wielding a sword, his shattered mind cycling through delusional personalities. Believing himself a Jedi Master, Bazil mistakes Lelila for his \"apprentice Traxari\" and Vek for an enemy, then accuses them both of serving the dark side. He collapses screaming, then rises as a cruel Imperial \"Commodore\" who calls Vek his brother \"Emanuel,\" prompting Vek to draw his blaster as Colonel Altair Quila and a security detail arrive. Finally Bazil sinks into a heartbreaking lucid fragment, mistaking Altair for his long-lost love Casey and believing himself blinded and imprisoned, pleading for help as a medical team moves in to treat the broken Intelligence director.",
